###Installing Helm on Ubuntu/Linux ###

step1 Download the Latest Helm Release:

	curl -O https://get.helm.sh/helm-v3.16.2-linux-amd64.tar.gz

step2 Extract the Package:

	tar xvf helm-v3.16.2-linux-amd64.tar.gz

step3 Move the Binary to /usr/local/bin:

	sudo mv linux-amd64/helm /usr/local/bin/helm

step4 Clean Up:

	rm helm-v3.16.2-linux-amd64.tar.gz
	rm -rf linux-amd64

step5 Verify the Installation:

	helm version
	which helm
